OL,6,FThe research, carried out by the
OL,7,Fcharity Hundred Families and shared
OL,8,Fexclusively with ITV News, reveals
OL,9,Fthat each year an average of 65
OL,10,Fmentally ill people carried out
OL,11,Fkillings.
OL,13,FIn some cases, the perpetrator killed
OL,14,Fmore than one person, so the number of
OL,15,Fvictims will be even higher.
